*Home Maintenance & Improvement Price Estimates:*
*1. Finish Winterization of Doors:*
• *$150:* This seems low for _all_ doors. It's more likely $150 _per_ exterior door if it includes weatherstripping, threshold inspection/repair, and potentially a sweep installation. Clarify the scope with the homeowner.
*2. Electrical:*
• *Check Lights:* $75 - $150 (depending on complexity).
• *HVAC/Bathroom Fan Issue:* $150 - $400 (diagnosis and minor repair. Could be higher for complex issues like motor replacement).
*3. Front Door Doorknob Replacement (Downstairs):*
• *$50 - $100 (hardware provided by homeowner):* This is a good estimate for a standard doorknob replacement.
*4. Vent Installation:*
• *Measurements for Vent Installation:* Included with installation or $50-$75 trip charge if standalone.
• *Vent Installation over Pocket Door:* $300 - $450 (including materials).
*5. Thermal Camera Inspection:*
• *$150:* As quoted.
*6. Rust Above Shower:*
• *Minor Rust Removal/Treatment:* $100 - $200.
• *Significant Rust/Tile Repair/Replacement:* $300+ (potentially much higher depending on the extent of damage).
*7. Exterior Door Replacement:*
• *Metal Door:* $800 - $1500+ (including installation).
• *Fiberglass Door:* $1000 - $2500+ (including installation).
*8. Mailbox Mounting on Brick Wall:*
• *$100 - $250 (including basic mailbox):* Higher-end mailboxes will increase the cost.
*Important Considerations:*
• *On-Site Assessment:* Highly recommended for all but the simplest tasks (e.g., doorknob replacement) to get accurate quotes.
• *Material Costs:* Clearly communicate with the homeowner who is responsible for material purchases.
• *Service Fees/Trip Charges:* Factor in any applicable service fees or trip charges.
• *Local Market Rates:* These estimates can vary based on location. Ensure they align with your local market.
By providing these detailed estimates and clearly outlining the variables that can affect pricing, you'll build trust and transparency with the homeowner.

$6,950 labor and materials

*1006 O St NW heating system estimate*

• Turn off tankless water heater
• Turn off HVAC system
• Turn off the water to the house (using main water shut off typically in basement)
• Drain entire plumbing system (including the heating loop)
• Desolder the hydronic heating coil from the plumbing system
• Remove and dispose of the failed heating coil
• Cut 3/4" copper pipes and Install two quarter turn shut off valves to the inbound cold water inlet on the tankless water heater
• Install a 3M scale inhibitor cartridge between the two newly installed shut off valves (this will help prevent scaling on the tankless water heater and the hydronic heating coils to help maintain peak efficiency)
• Remove the existing AC induction motor circulation pump (including plumbing and electrical) and dispose
• Install a new electronically commuted brushless ultra high efficiency circulation pump (including plumbing and electrical)
• Install new Unico 100K BTU hydronic heating coil
• Install automatic bleeding valve to prevent air in the hydronic heat loop
• Turn the water back on to the house and bleed all plumbing outlets and the hydronic heating loop
• Turn back on the tankless water heater and test
• Turn back on HVAC system and test

replies.text:
To perform a factory reset on a Rheem tankless water heater, follow these steps. The exact process may vary slightly depending on your model, but this is the general method for most Rheem units:

Locate the Control Panel:
Many Rheem units have a small digital control panel on the front or near the bottom of the unit.

Power Off the Unit:
Turn off the unit using the power button or by unplugging it from the power outlet.
1. Press and Hold the Reset Buttons:
    a. Locate the “Up” and “Down” buttons (typically arrows) and the “Mode” button on the control panel.
    b. Press and hold both the “Up” and “Down” buttons simultaneously, then also press the “Mode” button while continuing to hold the other buttons.
    c. Restore Power:
While holding the buttons, plug the unit back in or turn the breaker back on.
• Wait for the Reset Process:
• Hold the buttons for about 10-15 seconds until you see the display screen reset or change. This typically indicates that the unit has restored factory settings.
• Release the Buttons:
Let go of the buttons once the reset process completes.
• Confirm Reset:
The control panel should display default settings or clear any previous error codes.

After the Reset:
• Reconfigure Settings: If you customized temperature or operational settings, you will need to set them again.
• Check for Error Codes: See if any error codes return; if they do, there may still be a mechanical or operational issue that needs addressing.
If the steps don’t work or the model doesn’t support a manual reset, refer to your specific Rheem unit manual or contact Rheem Customer Support at 1-800-4<tel:1-800-432-8373|32-8373 (as sh>own on the sticker in the image).
